 95% of the people above lvl 45. Everyone did a great job, you were awesome <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Even if we had 3 clerics, one bard and 3 wizzies with Ice Comet we did a great job and I hope that everyone enjoyed the raid. <br><br>Special thanks to Ameron (wtg Boss <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) for leading the raid, he was an excellent leader even if this was his first time against Naggy. <br><br>Also, I would like to thank the Council of Guilds for giving the opportunity to The Silent Watch to lead this raid. I need to mention that it was our first time as dragon raid leaders. We might have many things to learn before the next one but the outcome, even if we had many loses, was that finally Lord Nagafen was killed. <br><br>Oh, I almost forgot about the loot, I am quite excited now hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Naggy droped the following items:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Blight, Hammer of the Scourge<br>Hierophant's Crook<br>Bladestopper<br>Gold Plated Koshigatana<br>Red Dragonscale<br>Treasure Hunter's Satchel</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>We own Nagafen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>See yas out there...<br> <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#004080">Balendin MacLeod</B></FONT><BR><I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#a0a0a0">Officer of the Silent Watch</I></FONT><BR><I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#a0a0a0">51 Cavalier</I></FONT><P></TD></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udoger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Doger</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 6:45:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Dead :)</span><hr size=1> Congratulations you guys! Well done! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Dogedme Kingson<br>Seekers of Knowledge<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uqiladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qiladin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 8:15:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mmcable.com/qiladin/Qpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Dead :)</span><hr size=1> Great fun!!!  Everyone did well.  Especially when we had a FG pop through the wall and bring back 3 or 4 friends.  Everyone kept their cool, assisted and we prevailed.  I don't want to speak for Masamune, but I am pretty sure she had just as much fun as I did charming the extra few FG we had and making them help us instead of pounding us.<br><br>In the end we prevailed over the Lord himself, although I wish there was an extra FG around to charm and sick on him, otherwise I felt a bit useless after the buffing was done.  But Lord Nagafen fell in the end, Mission Accomplished!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Qiladin Mindwarp &lt;The Silent Watch&gt;<br>52 Enchanter Karana<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uqiladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qiladin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 12/8/00 8:16:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujorywolfborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jory Wolfborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 8:15:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Missed the raid</span><hr size=1> Sorry I missed the raid guys, I guess I hadn't read enough of the original thread to see that we were that close to getting to Naggy in the rotation. I logged on today to see if we were up and lo and behold we had already killed him, the ironic thing is I actually was on with Jory yesterday too bad nobody contacted me, guess I will be stuck at 52 for another few weeks at least. *sigh* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usulaspsychoblades.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sulas Psychoblades</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 8:46:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Dead :)</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the raid guys I had a great time and was pleased to see him fall again. I think I can speak for some of my FoR guildmates in saying they had a great time also. Thanks for giving them a chance to come on a naggy raid also it was a good first time experience for many of them. Thanks again you guys were great. For only 3 clerics and 3 wizzies, losses were expected but this had to be picture perfect in my book. Great job everyone and thanks again! <p>=================================<BR>Sulas Psychoblades<BR>Fire of Redemption<BR>"Death Dealer Supreme"<BR>Rogue of the 51st Cycle<BR>Karana Server<BR><BR>"Death comes to us all, it's just a matter of time. The only thing that you need to worry about at the moment is that dark figure in the shadows."<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uameron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ameron</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 9:59:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Its harder than it looks.</span><hr size=1> First of all, thank you to everyone who attended, it was hard work but the majority of people covered eachothers backs great.<br>We stuck to the overall plan of how to take him down and it worked perfectly. <br>I was amazed how hard it was to organise groups, I wasnt expecting that many people and with it being a COG raid I tried not to refuse anyone.<br><br>We were hoping to have killed Naggy by about 1am GMT but it was past 4am after the lotto, so lots of us were probarby asleep at work today.<br>TSW is a 50/50 UK-europe/US guild so we are used to strange play times.<br>With Nag rotation being erratic to say the least the raid was a last minute alert. <br><br>Finaly well done to all of you, again I was proud and honored to lead this raid and if invited to I will do so again (as long as its not on a weekend).<br><br>Ameron Darkoak<br>GM The Silent Watch<br>www.thesilentwatch.com<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 10:19:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/seyil/villa/pippirun.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Dead :)</span><hr size=1> Congrats!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>It is a heckload of work organizing 8 groups of people to accomplish a goal - Ameron, if you have any tips on how to organize so many people at the same time, I would like to hear them! <br><br>pip <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarkahndreamhaunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArkahnDreamhaunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 2:14:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Naggy hath been slain</span><hr size=1> Lord Nagafen has been slain by CoG!  It was a successful raid, and took about 4 hours all in all.  Most of the time was spent right outside naggy's lair buffing and getting prepared.  After about 30 minutes of owning fire giants, we moved on to the magus fire giant.  Right after the magi was pulled (dropped Rokyl's channeling crystal) by a very courageous monk who almost lost his life, we finally went into the lair of the beast.  The healers waited back while the tanks went in, only leaving for a short heal if below 40% health, until naggy was at about 40% health, when the nukers went into to destroy him.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uameron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ameron</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/8/00 3:47:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Some things I knoticed that may help.</span><hr size=1> When I was forming groups I set one up with debuffing and pets in mind, thier job was once the tanks had managed to get a good agro on Naggy, to use any and all mana to debuff him.<br>Part of this process was to land a necro disease dot on him, no matter what level the dot is, it stops regen dead, Naggy regens somthing like 400 hp a tic if thats any indication of how vital that is to stop.<br>Plus I knoticed a HUGE differance in damage from his fire, I was taking only about 200 damage, when others with lower resistances were taking so much more.<br>The fear got alot of us, but it seems to have a save per tic, so with high magic resistance you dont go that far.<br>Would have been nice to have SoV since we had alot of rangers and +10 all resist discapline would have been handy.<br><br>Ameron <p></p><i></i><